git -->distributed  version control system 

working environments--> dev ,qa,uat,sit(system integration testing ),performance testing

Topics --> Git init,add,status,commit -m "msg",log,push origin,branch,branch branchname,
checkout branchname,clone,remote add fb(alias name) githuburl,remote -v,show commitid,show --pretty="" --name-only commitid,clean.clean -f,reset(SA TO WA),reset filename,
revert commitid (updated content , files going to delete in particular commit id),branch -d,branch -m newbranchname(modify),merge branchname,stash,stash apply,stash pop,
stash drop,pull origin , rebase vs merge


git commit -m "feature branch msg wrong commit" -->commit files which are in staging area 
git commit --amend -m "now updated commit message"--> changes most recent commit only 

NOTE : fb is remote repo url alias name

Difference of branch
--------------------
git diff branchname(comparision with current  branches)
git diff stag branchname(comparision b/w 2 branches )
git branch -r (display remote repo branches)
git branch -a(display all branches)
git branch -d branchname (delete a branch)
git push fb -all(push all local repos to remote)
git push fb dev qa (specific branches only move to remote repo)

Difference of Tags
-------------------
git tag (display all tags)
git tag tagname(create tag)
git push fb tag tagname(local to remote repo pushing)
git tag -d tagname (delete a tag)

stash 
-----
git stash (pause)
git stash apply(resume)

rebase vs merge
---------------
we can integrate changes from one branch to another by using rebase and merge cmnds
dev to master when we use merge means it will not display commitid only single commit id we can see
dev to master when we use merge means it will  display commitids history

.git ignore
------------
we can place files in this folder it will not commit the files 

readme.md 
----------
it is a file for understanding our repository we write some content in it like what steps to perform in this repository   

github-->repository management tool 
